post_text:
We have received the following questions:

Q: If I register for the Cardinal Cyber Academy can my student still attend in person?

A: If a student registers to attend the Cardinal Cyber Academy for the 2020-21 school year, they will be enrolled in this school with a semester commitment. After a semester, you may request to have your student attend school in a building.

Q: Do I have to register for the Cardinal Cyber Academy incase we go to emergency remote learning?

A: If the pandemic risk factors change for a classroom, building or district no registration is needed.

Canfield Police Department is with Canfield Local School District.
March 24 at 4:16 PM ·

Officer Lamping and Officer Garstka serve as School Resource Officers for Canfield Schools. They will be filming story time and we will be uploading to our page! Special thanks goes out to Canfield Schools for letting us grab a few books from the library to get started!

If your children have any special requests, please add them to the comments and we'll try to accomodate.

The blooper reel is also coming together nicely and will be released at a later date - "Humor can be one of our best survival tools" - Allen Klein

post_text: The Canfield Local School District will be delivering all curriculum K-12 online beginning Tuesday, March 17, 2020. K-8 students who are unable to access the curriculum online may pick up a packet from their school between 9:00 a.m. -3:00 p.m. on Tuesday. Please call your building administrator to make alternate arrangements if necessary. If you do not have access to a computer or wifi, please contact your building administrator as soon as possible. Teachers will be making contact with all students using email, phone calls, or communication applications. Please refer to our FAQ’s on the district website for additional details. The website will remain the central source for all communications. Thank you.

post_text: The Canfield Local School District will be closed on Monday, March 16, for students. All events and extra-curricular activities are suspended until further notice. Administrators and teachers are continuing to work on the plan this weekend for our students to be educated online or with blended instruction. This instruction will begin on Tuesday, March 17. We will update you on Monday with complete details. We will use our website as the hub of all communication. Students who do not have access to the internet or a computer should call their building administrator as soon as possible. Thank you for your patience and understanding.
